  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Consider the following code:\n\n``` js\n  var thing = <g> \n    <line x1=\"0\" x2=\"100\" y1=\"-2775.7\" y2=\"-2775.7\" stroke=\"red\" />\n  </g>;\n  React.render(thing, this.g);\n\n  var thing = <g> \n    <line x1=\"0\" x2=\"100\" y1=\"-2775.7\" y2=\"-2775.7\" stroke=\"red\" />\n    <line x1=\"0\" x2=\"100\" y1=\"-2770.7\" y2=\"-2770.7\" stroke=\"red\" />\n  </g>;\n  React.render(thing, this.g);\n```\n\nThe first line is rendered in `http://www.w3.org/2000/svg` `namespaceURI` but the second one in `http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml`. If you skip the first rendering it works.\n",
